<p><strong>TOEFL</strong></p>
<p>The TOEFL iBT is the Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL)&nbsp;<strong>Internet-based test (iBT)</strong>.</p>
<p>The TOEFL exam is administered by the Educational Testing Service numerous times each year throughout the world. For more information about testing centers,&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="extLink" href="http://www.ets.org/toefl" title="TOEFL Website" target="_blank">click here</a>&nbsp;to access the TOEFL Web site.</p>
<p><strong><strong>IELTS</strong></strong></p>
<p>The IELTS is the International English Language Testing System.</p>
<p>The IELTS is administered numerous times each year throughout the world. For more information about testing times and locations,&nbsp;<a class="extLink" href="http://www.ielts.org/" title="IELTS Website" target="_blank">click here</a>.</p>
<p><strong><strong>PTE</strong></strong></p>
<p>The PTE is the Pearsons Test of English.&nbsp; You may obtain more information&nbsp;<a href="http://www.pearsonpte.com/pteacademic/Pages/home.aspx" target="_self">here</a>.</p>
<p><strong><strong>English Language Help</strong></strong></p>
<p>BYU-Idaho does not have an ESL (English as a Second Language) program. If TOEFL requirements are not met, students are encouraged to increase their skills and retest. To learn more about the TOEFL exam, please visit&nbsp;<a class="extLink" href="http://www.ets.org/" title="http://www.ets.org/" target="_blank">www.ets.org</a>.</p>
<p>The English Language Center at Brigham Young University may also be able to help you improve your skills so that you may come to BYU-Idaho in the future. Learn more about this program by visiting&nbsp;<a href="http://elc.byu.edu/">http://elc.byu.edu</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Application Checklists</strong></p>
<p>These checklists are provided to assist you in the application process. Please select your current situation:</p>
